<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>RADIATOR/COOLING SYSTEM SERVICE MANUAL - PROSTAR&#8482; - COOLING PACKAGE COMPONENTS - POWER STEERING OIL
        COOLER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>POWER STEERING OIL COOLER</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The power steering oil cooler is secured to the back of the hood crossmember and can be accessed from
                under the chassis with the tilt-away bumper in the raised position.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Power Steering Oil Cooler - Removal</title>
            <figure id="f1202135" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1202135.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 46. Power Steering Hoses</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. POWER STEERING OIL COOLER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. POWER STEERING HOSES</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a suitable container under the power steering oil cooler hoses to catch any oil
                    from the system.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect two power steering hoses at the power steering oil cooler.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cap ends of power steering hoses and power steering oil cooler.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1202136" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1202136.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 47. Power Steering Oil Cooler</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LOWER RADIATOR FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MOUNT BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. P-CLAMPS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. TILT-AWAY BUMPER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. POWER STEERING OIL COOLER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two bolts from P-clamps at front crossmember.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove power steering oil cooler from under the vehicle.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Power Steering Oil Cooler - Installation</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Inspect the power steering oil cooler prior to installation for damage.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install power steering oil cooler on front crossmember and secure P-clamps with two
                    bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202136">Figure 47, Items 2 and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the capped ends from the power steering hoses and power steering oil cooler.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect two power steering hoses to the power steering oil cooler (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1202135">Figure 46, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Fill the power steering reservoir and check for leaks.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
